Speaker 2: Okay, and do you have the prescription in front of you?

Speaker 2: the delivery mechanism system and how it releases in the body.

Speaker 1: So do take it on an empty stomach for the best results.

Speaker 2: I'm going to send you a quantity of 20 to replace the ones you have there.

Speaker 1: You can keep the ones you have.

Speaker 2: There's nothing wrong with them, per se.

Speaker 1: improve it.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: So if I heard you correctly, it's going to say 100 on it, not AGV?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I've seen that, too.

Speaker 2: that says AGV.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 1: It'll say 100 on it.

Speaker 1: Oh, yes.

Speaker 2: Absolutely.

Speaker 1: Going forward, you won't have any issues with that.

Speaker 2: I'm going to message the pharmacy and make sure that the prescription is changed so that

Speaker 1: you never receive the generic going forward.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 2: Am I going to be billed for a new order of Viagra AGV or no?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So this order I'm sending you, obviously, I'm sending to you at no cost.

Speaker 1: Zero cost.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Because I'm replacing the order that you have there that you should have received.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: That's what I wanted to make sure.

Speaker 2: Yeah, of course.

Speaker 1: So zero cost for that, for the new order.

Speaker 2: And then moving forward, is it the same price or is there a different price or anything

Speaker 1: like that that I need to be aware of?

Speaker 2: No, it'll be the same price going forward if you just wish to continue.

Speaker 1: And your prescription comes with refills available.

Speaker 2: So as our customer, we're not a subscription.

Speaker 1: You can set up your account however works best for you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Is that my next question?

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: We do have customers that like to get their refills once a month, but we have customers

Speaker 2: that only get it twice a year.

Speaker 1: One order of 10 every six months and everything in between.

Speaker 2: And at any time, you can modify or change or delay an order or put a pause on your account

Speaker 1: for up to six months.

Speaker 2: We're really flexible in terms of that.

Speaker 1: We just recommend not canceling entirely because what that does, it cancels your prescription

Speaker 2: with refills.

Speaker 1: So when you call in again to place an order, we have to pay a doctor fee again to get a

Speaker 2: new prescription written.

Speaker 1: Great.

Speaker 2: So you do call in to get a refill.

Speaker 1: You don't have to mail in to get a refill, right?

Speaker 2: Is that what I'm hearing?

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: You can call in or I believe you can do it online, but I recommend calling in.

Speaker 1: But for now, what I'm going to do, I'm going to put a hold on it until August.

Speaker 2: So you have an opportunity to try the AGD and then you can determine how you want to

Speaker 1: set up your account going forward.

Speaker 2: Wonderful.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I think that answers all my questions.

Speaker 2: Should I still, I mean, I've tried Viagra before and I've tried CLS before and I've

Speaker 1: not had very much success with either.

Speaker 2: I'd like to try these because maybe these are better than the ones that I had received

Speaker 1: before.

Speaker 2: But I just, I don't know, I'm leery about taking pills because I know that sometimes

Speaker 1: they have complications, health complications.

Speaker 2: Is there anything I need to be aware of or look for?

Speaker 1: Well, you came to the right place because I understand that concern.

Speaker 2: There are so many things now in the market.

Speaker 1: It is really hard to figure out what you're getting and the legitimacy of it.

Speaker 2: But again, I assure you that we are FDA approved and so we are regulated.

Speaker 1: So the Viagra that we sell, there's no risk in terms of what you've probably heard

Speaker 2: about other pills out there that are very dangerous.

Speaker 1: I've heard of heart palpitations, color changes in your eyesight and things like that.

Speaker 2: I just want to make sure that this is safe and I'm not doing myself any harm.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: No, absolutely.

Speaker 1: It is safe to take.

Speaker 2: Like I said, with the new AGV, they've eliminated those side effects that people used to experience.

Speaker 1: So there shouldn't be any risk to you.

Speaker 2: So once the AGV does arrive, I should probably just toss these?

Speaker 1: Well, the ones you have there are also FDA approved.

Speaker 2: You can toss them if you want.

Speaker 1: If anything, they just may not work as well, but they're not harmful at all.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: My pleasure, sir.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Happy Valentine's and have a great weekend.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Happy Valentine's.

Speaker 2: Have a great day.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Thanks.
